parameters: Welcome...\n< Shopkeeper>

What's this, a child? If you want to
play, do it outside.\n< Shopkeeper>

I am not a child. I am a customer. I
also have an adventurer's license.\n< Serena>

I would like to purchase some equipment.
Could you show me what you have in
stock?\n< Serena>
...You do have money, right?\n< Shopkeeper>

Hmm... These items seem rather
unreliable... but I suppose they will
have to suffice for now.\n< Serena>

Oh ho. Calling my merchandise unreliable
is quite the statement. Got any
complaints about my products?\n< Shopkeeper>

Ah, no, I apologize. I spoke out of
turn. It's just that...\n< Serena>

Just that? "Just that I spoke the truth
without thinking"?\n< Shopkeeper>

Ugh... No. I apologize. I did not mean
to speak ill of the shopkeeper.\n< Serena>

It's just that for my purposes as a
weapon, this ring is insufficient.\n< Serena>

Ha... Weapon? Now you're talking about
weapons?\n< Shopkeeper>

When we say "weapon," we're talking
about swords, axes, things made of iron
like this.\n< Shopkeeper>

It's troublesome when people mix up
fairy tales with reality and then
complain about my goods.\n< Shopkeeper>

...The fact remains a fact. I use rings
as weapons. Your swords and axes cannot
withstand my magic power.\n< Serena>

Still going on about that! If you're so
sure, then try holding this.\n< Shopkeeper>

See for yourself how heavy, sturdy, and
dangerous this lump of iron is that
you're scoffing at. Compare it to that
ring of yours.\n< Shopkeeper>

If I prove that this sword is useless to
me, will you believe my story?\n< Serena>

Ha ha ha... Of course. If you can prove
that, I'll eat porridge out of my ass or
whatever else you say--\n< Shopkeeper>
Huh...?\n< Shopkeeper>

Cough... It was more fragile than I
thought...\n< Serena>

My apologies, shopkeeper. I've scattered
the fragments everywhere. Are you hurt?\n< Serena>

Ah... oh... you, what are you... a
witch...?!\n< Shopkeeper>

What's your intention coming here?! And
you've broken my valuable merchandise...
Compensate for it!\n< Shopkeeper>

...No. No, that's not it... Is this
sabotage?! Henry's doing...!\n< Shopkeeper>

No, that's not it. Ahh, why has it come
to this? I just wanted to shop...\n< Serena>

I'm sorry. I didn't mean to startle you.
Truly. I will compensate for the weapon
as well.\n< Serena>
CommonPopupManager.showInfo({},'100Ｇ Paid.',null)
Huh...?! A bag of gold coins...?\n< Shopkeeper>
Sorry, excuse me...\n< Serena>
Hey, wait... Hold on! All this money--\n< Shopkeeper>

Sigh... That was surprising... Is
conversation always this difficult?\n< Serena>

No, now that I think about it, it was my
first time engaging in an equal
conversation with a merchant.\n< Serena>

It's completely different from speaking
through a servant... Perhaps that's why
I angered him.\n< Serena>

Anyway, I've acquired the ring. Now I
can proceed with the quest.\n< Serena>
\n< Serena>Let's go to the guild.
\n< Serena>...

parameters:
Welcome... oh, it's just you, young
lady. As for a ring beyond that one—\n< Shopkeeper>

Forgive me, but that's not what I'm here
for right now. Excuse me.\n< Serena>

I'm actually here for something else. I
need to ask for a breastplate...\n< Serena>

A breastplate? Of course, I have those,
but finding one that fits you might
be...\n< Shopkeeper>

No, when I say breastplate, I don't mean
armor... it's more like...\n< Serena>

Something for the... delicate parts of
the chest... something soft...\n< Serena>

Ah, you mean a bra? If that's what
you're looking for, try the tool shop
next door.\n< Shopkeeper>

...I did go there, but nothing suited my
skin.\n< Serena>

You're an arms dealer, aren't you? If
you can make weapons, surely you can
make undergarments as well.\n< Serena>

...You say that so casually... but bras
and weapons are quite different genres,
you know.\n< Shopkeeper>
Well, I can make it though.\n< Shopkeeper>
Oh!\n< Serena>

But don't expect it to look pretty.
It'll be more like an extension of
armor.\n< Shopkeeper>
That's more than enough!\n< Serena>
Then wait here for a bit.\n< Shopkeeper>

Lucky for you, there's a roll of silk
left over. How about this?\n< Shopkeeper>

Ah, ...yes. I can tolerate this kind of
texture.\n< Serena>

So you can finally tolerate it, huh?
Just so you know, this is top-quality
stuff...\n< Shopkeeper>

Well, alright. Hold the other side for
me.\n< Shopkeeper>

Sew the corners, thread it through, flip
it over and—\n< Shopkeeper>
Thread the strings through and voilà.\n< Shopkeeper>
Hmm... oh, oh...?\n< Serena>

There, done. I think this size should be
just right... how about it?\n< Shopkeeper>

Impressive workmanship... Perhaps you're
more suited to be a tailor than a
blacksmith.\n< Serena>

Always with the extra comment... Any
housewife could do this much.\n< Shopkeeper>

Anyway, go try it on in that private
room over there.\n< Shopkeeper>
Hmm... yes.\n< Serena>

Now then, let's see if this cheeky
little missy actually needs a bra or
not.\n< Shopkeeper>

Hmph hmph hmph hmph. Just as I thought,
a slender and uninteresting body, huh?\n< Shopkeeper>

Flat as a board and yet you have the
nerve to ask for a bra. You're a decade
too early for that.\n< Shopkeeper>

...Heh, heh... such a meager... not even
worth peeping at...\n< Shopkeeper>
...!\n< Shopkeeper>

...What whiteness... Petite but...
there's flesh on that ass...\n< Shopkeeper>
This is...\n< Shopkeeper>

...Yes. It's a bit stiff and slightly
large, but within an acceptable range.\n< Serena>

Shopkeeper, this seems to be fine. Thank
you for accommodating my unreasonable
request.\n< Serena>
...\n< Shopkeeper>
Shopkeeper...?\n< Serena>
Huh? Oh...\n< Shopkeeper>
?... So, about the payment I owe you.\n< Serena>
M-Money?\n< Shopkeeper>

Ah, yes. That's right. Money, money,
yes.\n< Shopkeeper>

Let's see. After all, it's made of the
finest silk... Well... It'll be 100G.\n< Shopkeeper>
Understood. I shall pay.\n< Serena>
H-Huh...?\n< Shopkeeper>
What is it?\n< Serena>

100G, you know? That's a hundred gold
coins. It's enough to build a house. If
it were smaller, you could even buy a
ship with it.\n< Shopkeeper>

And you... that's right, the bag of gold
coins from the other day. There was also
100G in there.\n< Shopkeeper>

In total, that's 200G. Two houses, two
ships, you know? An enormous amount of
money. To handle such an amount so
casually...\n< Shopkeeper>
But, didn't you just say it was 100G...?\n< Serena>
...\n< Shopkeeper>
...Sigh...\n< Shopkeeper>

Ah, yes. 100G. I'll sell you that bra
for 100G.\n< Shopkeeper>
Very well. I shall pay.\n< Serena>
CommonPopupManager.showInfo({},'100Ｇ Paid.',null)
Y-Yes... Huh...\n< Shopkeeper>

What's the matter? You've been acting
strange...\n< Serena>

Ridiculous... It's becoming
ridiculous...\n< Shopkeeper>

To earn even a single gold coin, we have
to work from morning till sweat beads on
our foreheads, working and working...\n< Shopkeeper>

If we make one coin in a day, it's a big
profit. But most of it goes to living
expenses, and nothing much is left in
hand.\n< Shopkeeper>

And then, this kid... treats these
precious gold coins as if they're mere
pebbles or something...\n< Shopkeeper>
Hmm...?\n< Serena>

My apologies, have I done something
again to offend you, Shopkeeper?\n< Serena>
...\n< Shopkeeper>

No, no. It was a very fine transaction
indeed.\n< Shopkeeper>

There's no reason for dissatisfaction.
Please, come again anytime.\n< Shopkeeper>

Whether it's bras, panties, or
pacifiers. We'll prepare whatever we can
for you.\n< Shopkeeper>

Ugh... I'm definitely concerned about
the implications of his attitude...\n< Serena>

Well, it's fine. Shopkeeper... no, may I
have your name now?\n< Serena>
It's Gordon.\n< Gordon>
Gordon-san then. My name is Serena.\n< Serena>

I'll be counting on you for future
needs, Gordon- san.\n< Serena>

Ah, please do favor us with your
patronage. The fine-assed Serena-chan-
sama.\n< Gordon>
'　たった１００Ｇで問題は解決した。これで仕事を再開できる。ギルドへ行こう。'
